<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Don, Mem. Wern. Nat. Hist. Soc. vi. 59" authorityYear="1827" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Allium spurium" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spurium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Allium spurium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is occasionally confused with 
<taxonomicName family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. spirale" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="spirale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. spirale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its more or less similar growth habit, but the most distinctive characters include narrower leaf blades and scapes and smaller floral parts (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 3" captionStartId="T3" captionText="Table 3. Comparison of major characters of Allium section Rhizirideum in South Korea and northeastern China." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/AF867E5A3B86068A65AC72BC5A6CFB14" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableUuid="AF867E5A3B86068A65AC72BC5A6CFB14">3</tableCitation>
; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Comparative photographs of the inflorescence, cross-section of leaf and scape, flower, and tepal and filament arrangement of Allium section Rhizirdeum in South Korea and northeastern China A-E A. dumebuchum (H. J. Choi 201008 - 001) F-J A. spirale (H. J. Choi 191010 - 01) K-O A. spurium (H. J. Choi 200831 - 01) P-T A. minus (H. J. Choi 080063) U-Y A. senescens (H. J. Choi 080119)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.176.63378.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/531582" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1L-N</figureCitation>
). This species is newly recorded for South Korea, and the new vernacular name 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘Gak-si-du-me-bu-chu’">'Gak-si-du-me-bu-chu'</normalizedToken>
is given. Besides, Cheongnyangsan of South Korea is the disjunct southernmost limit for geographical distribution of 
<taxonomicName family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. spurium" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="spurium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. spurium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Distribution map of Allium dumebuchum and its related species section Allium dumebuchum Rhizirideum in Korea and northeastern China (revised from Sinitsyna et al. 2016)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.176.63378.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/531586" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
